<b>Alma:</b> "<i>O divina virtus...</i>"
<b>Narration:</b> I recite the incantation just as I'd read it, putting the full might of my power into each syllable. 
<b>Alma:</b> "<i>...quam reus curriculo mortis mortales sumus!</i>"
<b>Alma:</b> (I've never felt like this before...!)
<b>Narration:</b> Power flows through me like an electric current. 
<b>Alma:</b> <i>...Obsecro te. Obsecro te. Obsecro te...</i>
<b>Gus:</b> <i>Squeak!</i>
<b>Narration:</b> Gus' cheers invigorate me. I continue chanting, letting my voice boom throughout the shop.
<b>Alma:</b> <i>Per tuam potentiam et misericordiam...</i>
<b>Alma:</b> <i>...lapsos possim...</i>
<b>Alma:</b> <i>...suscitare!</i>
<b>Narration:</b> The cauldron boils over, exploding a mess of effervescent water onto the floor.
<b>Narration:</b> I barely hear Jonah's gasp over the flowing water.
<b>Jonah:</b> "...!"
<b>Narration:</b> Above the cauldron rises a luminous presence.
<b>???:</b> "..."
<b>Narration:</b> It's... Beautiful. Whatever it is.
<b>Narration:</b> A confounding energy radiates through me as I stare at the ball of light.
<b>Jonah:</b> "Simon...?"
<b>Narration:</b> With one simple word, the light begins to dim and a face I can barely percieve emerges beyond it.
<b>Narration:</b> The energy remains buzzing around in me, shaking me up inside. I wonder if Gus and Jonah can feel it, too.
<b>???:</b> "...Jonah?"
<b>Narration:</b> Jonah smiles a wide, toothy grin, big enough for me to see underneath his beard.
<b>Narration:</b> I smile, too.
